<TEXT>
THE International Amateur Athletic Federation has over-ruled a decision by the
South African governing body to lift a three-month drugs ban on javelin thrower
Philip Spies, who tested positive for a banned stimulant in September. The IAAF
has rejected an Athletics South Africa plea to the effect that the banned
substance was contained in a vitamin supplement taken with their approval.
</TEXT>
