<TEXT>
PETER Phillips, son of the Princess Royal, will win his first Scottish Schools
cap when he plays against French Schools at Goldenacre on December 22.
Phillips owes his inclusion in part to an injury to his Gordonstoun team-mate,
Fergie Gladstone. The other and perhaps more direct factor influencing his
selection was the decision to move Jason White from blindside flanker to lock,
his international position last season.
