<DATE>951130</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Honour for Neef</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>35</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126623</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SCOTLAND'S leading female sprinter, Melanie Neef, last night collected the
George Dallas award - in memory of the former Herald athletics correspondent -
from British Athletics Federation chairman Peter Radford at a ceremony in
Glasgow, writes Doug Gillon.
However, Europa Cup 400 metres champion Neef's Olympic hopes may be blighted by
economic problems. The sport's demands have forced her to abandon her job, and
although her former employers continue to provide a car, she feels guilty about
keeping it.
``I don't enjoy full-time athletics, and would like some part-time work, and a
car, until Atlanta,'' she said.
</TEXT>
