<TEXT>
Go-home pact
CAIRO: The leaders of Burundi, Rwanda, Uganda, and Zaire have signed an
agreement which former US President Jimmy Carter said would speed up the return
home of Rwandan refugees. More than one million Rwandans are in camps in Zaire
and Tanzania following last year's genocidal civil warn camps in Zaire and
Tanzania following last year's genocidal civil war.
