<TEXT>
q UP TO 5500 people are still missing from Srebrenica months after Serbs
encircled and captured the eastern Bosnian town, according to a new UN report.
``The best current estimate of the number of missing is perhaps between 3500
and 5500,'' said the report.
It was requested by the Security Council on November 9 following news reports
of executions, rapes, and other horrors when Bosnian Serbs overran the Muslim
enclave last July.
``This and other reports provide undeniable evidence of a consistent pattern of
summary executions, rape, mass expulsion, arbitrary detentions, forced labour,
and large-scale disappearances. The full horror has yet to be properly
investigated and revealed,'' said Secretary-General Boutros Boutros-Ghali.
</TEXT>
