<DATE>951130</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Trust plans holidays at spy station</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>9</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126641</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
A SPY station, which was part of the GCHQ communications network and tapped
into Soviet transmissions, is set to be transformed into a children's holiday
centre.
Discovery Camps Trust is seeking planning permission for the listening station
at Hawklaw near Cupar in Fife.
Chairman of the Dundee-based trust, Mr Webster Simpson, said: ``It's rather
nice to think the fruits of the cold war will be used to give children decent
holidays.''
A spokesman for North East Fife District Council's planning department
confirmed a planning application had been lodged.
A Ministry of Defence land agent said: ``We are currently clearing the site and
it will be advertised for sale soon.''
</TEXT>
