<BYLINE>Happy summons for a London bobby</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126648</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
HE is the London bobby that President Clinton never forgot. PC Laurie Mullin,
58, was the officer who showed the then Governor of Arkansas, his wife Hillary,
and their daughter Chelsea, around the House of Commons some six years ago. Mr
Mullin received a personal invitation to attend the President's reception at
the US Ambassador's residence in London's Regent's Park last night. Mr Mullin,
of Barking, Essex, who has been an officer at the Commons for 18 years, said:
``I am over the moon.''
</TEXT>
