<HEADLINE>Bombs found</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>1</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126650</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
Police said they found two suspected bombs in Belfast yesterday on the eve of
President Bill Clinton's visit to the city, the first by a serving  American
president.
One was found a few hundred yards from the hotel where Mr Clinton will stay
today and was blown up and a second  was found about one mile away. No-one
claimed responsibility for planting either device.
</TEXT>
