<TEXT>
Late for school: more than 400 years after it was founded, Edinburgh University
was presented yesterday with its original charter, to the delight of Mr Arnott
Wilson, university archivist, right, and Mr Charles Melville, conservator. The
document, granted by James VI in 1582, was handed over by Lord Provost Norman
Irons. It authorised councillors to spend old ecclesiastical revenues on a
college. Picture: MIKE WILKINSON
</TEXT>
