<DATE>951130</DATE>
<HEADLINE>A seagoing memorial to `an indomitable man'</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>3</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126665</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
AMERICA is to name a destroyer after wartime Prime Minister Winston Churchill.
President Clinton said the decision was to honour the Second World War alliance
between Britain and America .
He said: ``When that ship slips down the ways in the final year of this
century, its name will ride the seas as a reminder for the coming century of an
indomitable man who shaped our age, who stood always for freedom, who showed
anew the glorious strength of human spirit.'' The 9200-ton USS Winston
Churchill will be the 31st of the Arleigh Burke class of destroyers.
</TEXT>
