<HEADLINE>Macleod case is continued</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>1</EDITION>
<PAGE>11</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126693</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
CHARGES against Free Church of Scotland Professor Donald Macleod were continued
without plea for a further two weeks at Edinburgh Sheriff Court yesterday.
Professor Macleod, 55, of Craiglea Drive, Edinburgh, faces six allegations of
assault involving five women over a seven-year period dating back to 1985.
He is accused of carrying out four assaults at the Free Church College on The
Mound in Edinburgh, where he holds the chair of systematic theology, and the
remainder at his home and in a car parked at the Cameron Toll shopping centre
in Edinburgh.
Defence lawyer Eric Scott asked Sheriff Roger Craik, QC, for continuation until
December 13 to allow the defence time to prepare its case.
</TEXT>
