<DOCNO>GH951130-000157</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951130-000157</DOCID>
<DATE>951130</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Search for great Scot</HEADLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126697</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
VIRGIN boss Richard Branson pays a flying visit to Glasgow today to ask what
has become of the great Scottish entrepreneur.
As one of the UK's top entrepreneurs himself, he is expected to tell Scottish
business leaders that they have a key role to play in reversing a negative
attitude which exists in Scotland towards the spirit of enterprise.
``What Scotland needs is more Kwik-Fit and Scottish &amp; Newcastle type companies
if the economy is to prosper, said Mr Branson. ``But the only way that will
happen is to encourage the 18,19 or 20 year-olds to start a new business.''
Mr Branson is expected to repeat his message tonight at a dinner to launch The
Entrepreneurial Exchange, which is being described as the most ambitious bid
yet to turn Scotland into a nation of self-made business people.
</TEXT>
