<DOC>
<DOCNO>GH951130-000158</DOCNO>
<DOCID>GH951130-000158</DOCID>
<DATE>951130</DATE>
<HEADLINE>Shield sees sales grow</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>Robert Powell</BYLINE>
<EDITION>2</EDITION>
<PAGE>20</PAGE>
<RECORDNO>975126698</RECORDNO>
<TEXT>
SHIELD Diagnostics, the Dundee company which makes specialist kits to diagnose
a variety of medical conditions, is achieving strong sales growth, writes
ROBERT POWELL.
But problems with the supply of raw materials for its successful syphilis
diagnosis kit held back profits in the six months to September 30.
Pre-tax profits rose to #43,600 from #19,500, but were well below City
expectations. The share price, which rose 25p earlier this week in anticipation
of a good result, closed down 6p at 106p.
But with sales growing 21% to #2.73m at the half-way stage and six new products
due to be launched in the second half of the year, the prospects for Shield
Diagnostics look bright.
The hi-tech company was floated on the stock market in 1993 and broke into
profit for the first time last year. Founded by a group of medical researchers
at Dundee University, it has grown by acquisition.
Now Shield Diagnostics is developing a new technology which will allow fresh
blood to be tested for a variety of conditions without being centrifuged first
to produce serum.
Finance director David Evans said this rapid assay technology should reach
commercial production in 12 to 15 months.
In the more immediate future, Shield Diagnostic's commercial success hinges on
the results of a clinical analysis of a blood protein called factor XII.
Shield Diagnostics enjoyed strong demand during the first half for its syphilis
diagnosis kits and its auto-immune products, most of which detect rheumatic
diseases.
Although profits seem unlikely to grow much this year, the outlook for 1995-96
is more promising.
Greig Middleton is pencilling in a pre-tax profit of #900,000 on turnover of
#7m in 1996-97 and expects the company to continue growing by acquisition.
FACT FILE
Interim 1995 1994
Pre-tax profit #43,600 #19,500
Turnover #2.73m #2.26m
EPS 0.18p 0.10p
Dividend nil nil
</TEXT>
